rComments: Nice woman but very boring lecturer. Not a lot of information on the slides at the beginning of the year, monotone voice, highly interested in the term "life expectancy".
Best Professor I've ever had! I love this woman! The lectures were interesting and laid back and the class structure was great with 3 term tests and no assignments.
Must attend lecture as she does mention alot of stuff that are not included in the lecture slides that are posted. If u go to lecture + do the readings you can def do very very well.

Prof Silver's class is no doubt a bird course and is very easy as long as you study the lecture slides.(textbook not needed) She also always makes the lectures interesting without being content heavy and overwhelming. Will def that courses again with her!! Awersome!!

Prof. Silver makes boring topics on aging interesting.  Attendance is not mandatory but you have to attend the lectures, she writes things on the board and things that are not in the book.  I like how she ties things into the community and real world.  Very enthusiastic and caring about students.  I would recommend her class and take her again.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Clear grading criteria', 'Caring']

rComments: Professor Silver is funny and provides extensive information regarding each topic.  She is really open to questions and engages with us.  Learning about the elderly/health care system is more interesting than I expected and I think that it's like the because of how Professor Silver teaches.
Very clear and concise about what she expects of you for the course. Exams were mostly lecture based. Her lectures were admittedly a bit dry but she is quite approachable
Fantastic prof., great class, def recommend

Everything is right off her slides. Was only 5 textbook questions on the exam. Attend her lectures b/c she adds in extra slides that she does not post on blackboard. Lecture powerpoints is very important for the exams. Overall kinda boring but can get a good mark.
My favourite Prof!  I love taking her classes.  You have to go to the lectures and do the readings and you can do well.
Not an easy prof. but very helpful and caring especially if you show an interest in her research.
She is very approachable and friendly but she is also amazingly smart.  I have taken several classes with Prof.Silver nad I recommend them highly.

ANY class with her is DIRT easy. She reuses lecture slides for different classes, reducing the amount of new material you'd have to know. Her lectures are SO boring/dry, it's straight off the slides. Her exams are mostly lecture but she'll throw in a few textbook questions for the sake of putting them in there. She's a poor prof but an easy 80+

She's a really great prof, very easy to understand. Her exam was multiple choice and really based on her lectures, but reading the textbook definitely helped. Overall, very approachable and I aim to take her courses for HLT classes.

Another one of those really good, rare profs at UTSC! Very clear, in terms of both communication style and the exams which are MC. If you had to pick between studying the book or lecture notes, go for lecture notes since the majority of the exam is on that alone. Only about 20% was from the book. Good Luck.
I thought she was an ok prof in terms of lecture alot of info in them.  she used the text book alot!! was very easy to talk to about anything!
